  "description": [
    "Page 18 Odds 100 to 1 Italy Will Fight Effort to Halt Invasion League War on Duce Seen as Growing Possibility Brunt Would Be Borne by Britain By WILLIAM PHILIP SIMMS A League war against Italythe first of its kind in historyis seen here as a distinct and growing pos sibility If it comes experts are asking how and where will it be fought who will do the fighting and what will be the outcome If the League resorts to force to block Mussolini in Ethiopia odds are quoted at 100 to 1 that II Duce will fight back Thus would begin one of the strangest conflicts in modern times It would be largely a war between Great Britain and Italy according to military and naval experts Other League powers would contribute financial support rather than active armed aid A possible exception to this might be France AIR AND WATER BATTLE Infantry is seen as having little to do save to stand byunless the con flagration spreads to Europe Italys land frontiers of course would have to be closed The British fleet and air force therefore would likely be the Leagues chief weapons Italian experts share this view but are"
